##Li Wenliang, a whistle-blower with new pneumonia, says truth is more important than rehabilitation

Micro signal

Function introduction, real-time, original, professional financial news distribution center. In an age of information overload, you need to choose

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Li Wenliang, a 34-year-old ophthalmologist at Wuhan Central Hospital, was the first to reveal the condition of the pneumonia. He was retweeted with screenshots and then interviewed by the authorities and admonished by the police. During the course of his treatment, he was infected himself, as were several colleagues and parents. Photo provided by interviewees

Wuhan Doctor Li Wenliang is the first to disclose the unknown pneumonia related situation, by the unit interview, the police admonition. He did not know if he was one of the eight "rumormongers" being investigated. He said it was more important for people to know the truth than to rehabilitate themselves, and that a healthy society should not have only one voice

By Ken Tan

It was good news for Li Wenliang, who was admitted to the hospital 18 days later, that his nucleic acid test was negative. He still lies in an isolation ward in the respiratory and intensive care unit of Wuhan General Hospital, where he relies on doctors and nurses to take care of him.
Instead, he was treated under the label "pneumonia of unknown origin. ". It is an infectious disease that has now been shown to be "human-to-human" , and the epidemic continues to spread at an accelerating rate. As of 2400 hours on January 30, China had 9,692 confirmed cases and 15,238 suspected cases.

Li Wenliang, an ophthalmologist at Wuhan's Central Hospital, tried to tell his classmates about the dangers he learned about at work, but did not want to "Jinx" an "illegal act" .

A month ago, at 17:48 on December 30, Li Wenliang posted a message to a group of about 150 students: "seven SARS cases have been confirmed in the south China fruit and seafood market, and they are under quarantine in the Emergency Department of our hospital. ". On the same day, the "urgent notice on doing a good job in the treatment of pneumonia of unknown cause" issued by the Wuhan Municipal Health Commission also circulated on the Internet, demanding strict information reporting, and stressed that "without authorization any unit, individuals may not release rescue information to the outside. ".

Li Wenliang in the wechat group of reminders opened the mouth. A group friend posted a screenshot of his conversation online, but left out the most crucial information: His name and occupation. This led screenshots to his precise location, and soon after he was interviewed by the hospital's Inspector General's office, he went to the district police station on January 3 and signed a "warning letter" warning of "illegal problems. ".

After January 20, as the new crown pneumonia epidemic spread rapidly, the story of a man who had been labeled by the police as a source of false information was taken as a footnote to the front line medical staff in the outbreak: He was infected during a visit to the clinic, he was in the ICU for a while. In addition, several of his colleagues and parents were also infected with COVID-19 pneumonia.

When the public traced back to the source of the epidemic only to find that there had been early warning, Li Wenliang because of its screenshot on the real name and became able to be found "whistle-blower. ". He said he was just trying to remind his classmates, but did not think so much. He was angry when the screenshots were circulated, but the public was relieved out of concern for public health. Now it doesn't matter whether he is rehabilitated or not, because the truth matters more than that, and a healthy society should not have only one voice.

Along with Li Wenliang, there were eight rumour mongers previously reported by Wuhan Police. The news that they had been investigated and punished once made the CCTV news. Li said he did not know if he was one of the eight. Caixin noted that the Wuhan Public Security Bureau's Official Weibo "Ping an Wuhan" first reported that it had summoned eight lawbreakers at 17:38 on January 1, while Li Wenliang said he first went to the police station on the morning of January 3. On January 29, when Wuhan Police reported the incident for the second time, they did not mention Li's disciplinary punishment.

In addition to Li Wenliang, the CAIXIN reporter also contacted a person, also a doctor, who was allegedly sent an alert on the wechat group and then retweeted a screenshot. The woman, who did not want to be named, declined CAIXIN's request for an interview, and it was not clear whether she was one of the eight "rumormongers. ". She responded that she did not want to talk about it because the focus was now on raising supplies for the hospital.

On January 30, Li Wenliang gave an interview to Caixin under his real name. He is from Liaoning. He is 34 years old. He said he wanted to go to college in the south because he didn't like the Society of acquaintances and the world. In 2004, he took the Gaokao, a seven-year program in clinical medicine, because he wanted a "more stable major" . He enrolled in the Wuhan University. After graduating, he worked in Xiamen for three years before returning to Wuhan in 2014, where he has been working at Wuhan's Central Hospital ever since.

Following is a dialogue between Li Wenliang and a reporter from CAIXIN.

"apparently, there is a human-to-human relationship. "

Reporter: How are you now?

Li Wenliang: I received Standard Treatment in the respiratory and intensive care unit, a four-person isolation ward, currently only two people live, can keep in touch with the outside world by cell phone, usually by doctors and nurses to take care of me, every day the nurse would help to wipe the face and body. I heard the doctor today (30th) that my nucleic acid test results have turned negative, but this is the result of the throat swab, I do not think it represents the Alveoli. It takes a while for the lungs to function, but there's still some breathing difficulties, always needs high flow of oxygen, and can't eat much.

CAIXIN REPORTER: The public is very concerned about you in the group chat in the "confirmed 7 cases of SARS" , then what is the situation?

Li Wenliang: I was in a 150 or so students of the group, at that time also stressed not to spread, mainly want to remind the clinical work of students pay attention to protection. Because I also talked to my colleagues about this, although there were not so many cases at that time, but I was afraid that there would be an outbreak, that the epidemic would spread, because this virus is very similar to SARS.

Caixin reporter: Do you mean like SARS, like "people to people" ?

Li Wenliang: apparently there is a human-to-human relationship. Around January 8th, I treated these patients myself. At that time, we had a patient with acute angle-closure Glaucoma admitted to hospital, the day of poor appetite, but normal temperature. We didn't think anything of it at first, but then her glaucoma cleared and her pressure cleared, and the next day she still had no appetite, she had a fever at noon, and the CT scan of her lungs showed "viral pneumonia. " , the other markers are consistent with unexplained pneumonia.

The family that cared for her that night also had a fever, as did her other daughter, an obvious human-to-human transmission. We immediately reported to the Medical Service and hospital office, asked the hospital expert group consultation, after consultation patients in my ward isolation treatment. Three days later, we did a follow up CT, and it was still viral pneumonia, and it expanded, and it got worse, and then he was transferred to a suction isolation ward, and I don't know what happened after that.

CAIXIN REPORTER: Since at that time already appeared"person-to-person"circumstance, why is the case that diagnose so few?

Li Wenliang: At that time, it was difficult to confirm the diagnosis. The Kit had not come out yet. But no kit can be sent for nucleic acid testing, but more trouble time-consuming, I do not know the exact process. When our hospital panel consulted with the patient, they said they couldn't decide whether to do the test or not. At that time, the clinical diagnosis was made by ruling out other causes, such as CT findings, ineffective conventional therapy, low white blood cell count, and lymphocyte, which were all indicators.

CAIXIN: is your own infection also related to this patient?

Li Wenliang: At first the patient did not have a fever. I was careless and did not take precautions. The day the patient was transferred, I started coughing, the next day I had a fever, and that's when I started wearing an N95 mask. January 12, tested positive for respiratory virus, did a C.T. , and was hospitalized with a high suspicion of new coronavirus pneumonia. My colleagues in the same department also developed infections a day or two after me, and my parents were hospitalized three or four days after me. I went through a relapse and now take antibiotics, antiviral drugs, Globulin and oxygen every day.

CAIXIN: Do you have to pay for all these treatments yourself?

Li Wenliang: Immune Globulin is bought at one's own expense, some are drugstore to send over, some are schoolmates help to buy. I don't know if I'll be able to cover the sixty thousand I've spent so far. Some enterprises have launched a rescue plan for medical staff infection, originally intended to apply, but the nucleic acid test negative, it is not expected.

Caixin reporter: You mentioned just now in the group once stressed not to screenshot to spread out, but still spread out, how do you think?

Li Wenliang: that night, a lot of people on wechat asked me with screenshots. And they screenshots are not complete, originally in the "confirmed 7 cases of SARS" , I stressed that this is the coronavirus, the specific typing, but these screenshots of the network did not. I feel bad about this. I could be punished. Because this is sensitive information, and in the "two sessions" of the sensitive moment. I was angry. I didn't type the screenshot. Now see some light, others may also be in a hurry, in order to remind friends and family.

……
